HEADWORD: Sapindaceous
<hw>Sap`in*da"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to an order of trees and shrubs
(<ord>Sapindaceae</ord>), including the (typical) genus Sapindus, the
maples, the margosa, and about seventy other genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapindus</ent>⟦br⟧
